# UgaTaima Desert Map
#
# Symbols resolve via assets/tiles.yaml for the "desert" biome (see the
# data-driven legend in the map viewer for the authoritative list).
# Tiles used here:
# . = sand (walkable)   T = Sand Dune   A = Large Dune (blocking)
# R = Moss-covered Stone (corners)   W = oasis water (blocking)
# P = Desert Palm (blocking, environment sprite)
# Spawns / markers:
# n = bandit   @ = NPC / special-tile placeholder
# @ in the open desert = pyramid_entrance
# Dragon STATUES (4 corners): each is an NPC placeholder bound to a
# dragon_statue_* entry in npcs.yaml. Approaching one lets you spend a matching
# dragon statuette (looted from the pyramid) to SUMMON that dragon; the statue
# then vanishes. Black->dragon(fire), Red->dragon_red(dark),
# Green->dragon_green(poison), Gold->dragon_gold(air).
#
# Layout: a central oasis (desert merchant + red teleporter) plus two small
# palm oases, each guarded by 5 bandits (clearing an oasis's bandits drops a
# 500-gold chest at its water — see desert.clear_encounters in map_configs.yaml).
# MAIN QUEST: only these statue-summoned dragons count toward "dragon_slayer"
# (combat.go updateQuestProgress gates the credit on the summoned-dragon flag),
# so wild dragons elsewhere would NOT win the game.
